“The waves of the sea help me get back to me.” 

When I was full of chaos, she gave me peace. 

When I had low visibility, she gave me clarity. 

When I needed to learn, she gave me turtles, dolphins, and manta rays as mentors. 

When I needed to grow, she showed me that the currents and waves of life could make me stronger. 

The ocean and I have a relationship. 

All energy flows as one. 

So I ask you, why would I not stop to take care of her?

Why would I not stop to cherish her? 

Why would I not stop to do the same for myself? 

#mentalhealthmatters💙

When I look back in time I see both the happiness and the pain we all inevitably experience in life- love, loss, family, growth, heartbreak. 

But, when I look in the mirror I see strength, perseverance, beauty, character, and growing potential. 

We can’t control what happens to us in life - this is fact. 

We CAN control our reactions, our relationships with ourselves, how we treat others, how we choose to let things change us, and whether we decide to stay wounded or to grow wise. 

What are you choosing these days? 🧠

For those who have asked recently, I came back to Hawaii in May for vacation and ended up moving back. Shocker, I know. 🫣😬🤗

Florida was FUN - don’t get me wrong. I’m glad I finally got a chance to live in the mainland and know what it’s like. Guam isn’t even printed on half the maps I’ve seen, so this was quite the adventure for me. 🐊🎆 ⚡️

However, it felt like a limb was missing.

There is no denying that I am born, raised, and built to be on an island. 🧜🏼‍♀️🤷🏼‍♀️

There is nothing quite like the peace of knowing that I am right where I’m meant to be right now - for my career, my family, my personal interests, and my future. 💗

Let me stimulate your brain a lil’ bit: Have you found your soul spot yet? What feels like home to you? 🌎🌍🌏

Which eyes 👁️👁️ have your vote?
Blue, brown or Black and white?

Cheers to another trip around the sun☀️
